A4.text: Yokohama is the world's 31st largest seaport in terms of total cargo volume, at 121,326 freight tons as of 2011, and is ranked 37th in terms of TEUs (Twenty-foot equivalent units).

A5.text: The Port of Yokohama was officially opened on June 2, 1859.
